<bioghist>
<head>Biography</head>
<p>Charles Sperry Andrews III (1917-2005) was an artist who purchased and preserved the J. Alden Weir farm in 1957 after the death of Mahonri Young. The Weir Farm became a National Historic Site in 1990. He was married to Doris Bass Andrews.</p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent>
<head>Scope and Content of Collection</head>
<p>The Sperry Andrews Collection is a small collection containing a gallery program and postcards.</p>
</scopecontent>
